1
00:00:14,733 --> 00:00:16,133
Mom, I'm going to buy a phone.

2
00:00:16,200 --> 00:00:17,233
I'm just going to buy something,
Mom.

3
00:00:17,300 --> 00:00:18,700
My treat.

4
00:00:18,767 --> 00:00:20,967
Oh, wow! What a small world!

5
00:00:21,033 --> 00:00:22,333
Do I really have
to see you here?

6
00:00:22,400 --> 00:00:23,667
Can you afford this place?

7
00:00:23,733 --> 00:00:25,767
I'm sure you only have enough
money for transportation.

8
00:00:25,833 --> 00:00:27,967
I might not have money,
but I'm a good person.

9
00:00:28,033 --> 00:00:29,467
Unlike you, that has to drive
a big car

10
00:00:29,533 --> 00:00:32,300
to carry your horns and tail.

11
00:00:32,367 --> 00:00:34,300
She really makes
my blood boil!

12
00:00:34,400 --> 00:00:36,633
I've been asking you
what happened.

13
00:00:36,700 --> 00:00:37,900
But you were ignoring me.

14
00:00:37,967 --> 00:00:40,800
I saw the woman who killed
your brother.

15
00:00:40,867 --> 00:00:44,800
Even I don't know what
to tell them if I was there.

16
00:00:44,867 --> 00:00:46,167
I don't care if she's mad.

17
00:00:46,233 --> 00:00:51,000
But yelling out in public that
my mom is an e-convict is wrong.

18
00:00:51,067 --> 00:00:53,533
Red, it's so good to see you.

19
00:00:53,600 --> 00:00:54,800
I'm glad you're all better now.

20
00:00:54,867 --> 00:00:57,867
Sab, where are Yenyen
and Raichu?

21
00:00:57,933 --> 00:00:59,033
Did they get rescued, too?

22
00:00:59,100 --> 00:01:01,100
You disappoint me, Red.

23
00:01:01,167 --> 00:01:04,567
I thought you'd thank me
for saving your life.

24
00:01:04,633 --> 00:01:07,567
But all you think about
is Yenyen.

25
00:01:07,667 --> 00:01:08,733
Unbelievable.

26
00:01:10,067 --> 00:01:14,367
Coach used to say good people
are like candles.

27
00:01:14,433 --> 00:01:17,800
They burn themselves up
to give light to others.

28
00:01:17,867 --> 00:01:22,800
She gave light and
hope to Red and me.

29
00:01:22,867 --> 00:01:24,500
Red!

30
00:01:24,567 --> 00:01:26,100
Yen!

31
00:01:26,167 --> 00:01:27,667
Yenyen!

32
00:01:27,733 --> 00:01:31,400
Yeah, your dad told me
that Yenyen's been rescued.

33
00:01:31,467 --> 00:01:33,833
Yeah, actually,
she's with me right now.

34
00:01:33,900 --> 00:01:35,067
I want to meet her.

35
00:01:35,133 --> 00:01:36,900
Okay, we'll wait for you here.

36
00:01:36,967 --> 00:01:38,000
Where is she?

37
00:01:38,067 --> 00:01:39,433
Where's Yenyen?

38
00:01:39,500 --> 00:01:40,533
She just went to buy drinks.

39
00:01:40,600 --> 00:01:41,500
She'll be here in a little bit.

40
00:01:41,600 --> 00:01:42,600
Okay.

41
00:02:15,533 --> 00:02:20,067
God, please keep my daughter
away from harm.

42
00:02:22,767 --> 00:02:27,033
Don't let her cross paths
with Rina.

43
00:02:28,633 --> 00:02:30,367
I don't want my daughter
to get hurt

44
00:02:30,433 --> 00:02:33,200
and involved in Rina's wrath.

45
00:02:34,867 --> 00:02:40,700
God, I'm already asking
for forgiveness.

46
00:02:40,767 --> 00:02:42,033
I'm only human.

47
00:02:42,100 --> 00:02:47,600
If Rina hurts my daughter,
I will never back down.

48
00:02:49,133 --> 00:02:52,200
I took good care of Angelo,
her son.

49
00:02:52,267 --> 00:02:54,800
I never did anything
to hurt him.

50
00:02:55,900 --> 00:02:59,333
So she doesn't have the right
to hurt my daughter.

51
00:03:11,333 --> 00:03:15,067
I will get justice
for my son's death!

52
00:03:16,633 --> 00:03:20,367
I will make sure your mom
will rot in jail!

53
00:03:20,433 --> 00:03:22,667
They shouldn't have
let you out of jail!

54
00:03:22,767 --> 00:03:25,900
Did you know that this woman
is a murderer?

55
00:03:25,967 --> 00:03:27,767
She killed my son!

56
00:03:45,333 --> 00:03:46,900
Mom, wait here.
I'll check on her.

57
00:03:46,967 --> 00:03:48,267
- Okay.
- One sec.

58
00:04:22,900 --> 00:04:24,100
Red?

59
00:04:24,167 --> 00:04:25,567
Red, what's going on?

60
00:04:28,567 --> 00:04:30,600
I don't know what's going on,
to be honest.

61
00:04:34,200 --> 00:04:35,333
Where is she?

62
00:04:35,400 --> 00:04:37,900
She knows I'm coming, right?

63
00:04:37,967 --> 00:04:39,633
I know. I'm trying to find her.

64
00:04:53,700 --> 00:04:55,067
My mom is a nice person.

65
00:04:55,133 --> 00:04:57,100
She likes whoever I like.

66
00:04:58,133 --> 00:05:01,400
His parents raised him well.

67
00:05:01,500 --> 00:05:04,267
I'm sure you'll like him, Mom.

68
00:05:04,333 --> 00:05:05,633
Once I meet him...

69
00:05:07,867 --> 00:05:11,433
he will be a part of our family.

70
00:05:26,733 --> 00:05:28,267
Hey...

71
00:05:28,333 --> 00:05:29,233
what's with you?

72
00:05:29,300 --> 00:05:30,767
Why are you staring
into nothing?

73
00:05:30,833 --> 00:05:31,800
Where's Red?

74
00:05:32,767 --> 00:05:34,667
Don't tell me you had a fight
with him already.

75
00:05:36,133 --> 00:05:37,500
Raichu, Red is...

76
00:05:37,567 --> 00:05:38,800
Why? What happened to Red?

77
00:05:41,133 --> 00:05:42,667
What's going on?

78
00:05:42,733 --> 00:05:45,633
She just left without a word.

79
00:05:45,700 --> 00:05:46,633
I know what to do.

80
00:05:47,733 --> 00:05:48,700
Call her.

81
00:05:48,767 --> 00:05:49,967
Call her up.

82
00:05:50,033 --> 00:05:51,267
She doesn't have a phone.

83
00:05:52,900 --> 00:05:54,433
She doesn't have a phone?

84
00:05:55,567 --> 00:05:58,200
Red, is there someone who
doesn't have a cellphone?

85
00:05:58,267 --> 00:06:00,367
Even garbage collectors have it.

86
00:06:00,433 --> 00:06:01,900
How come she doesn't have one?

87
00:06:03,033 --> 00:06:04,600
I don't know, Mom.

88
00:06:04,667 --> 00:06:05,967
I'm confused too.

89
00:06:07,000 --> 00:06:08,933
I don't know why she
left all of a sudden.

90
00:06:09,033 --> 00:06:10,200
She left in a hurry.

91
00:06:12,733 --> 00:06:14,500
Don't you think she's shy?

92
00:06:14,567 --> 00:06:16,433
Well, I don't know.

93
00:06:16,500 --> 00:06:20,800
She was so nervous earlier.

94
00:06:20,867 --> 00:06:22,033
Why would she feel shy?

95
00:06:22,100 --> 00:06:23,100
Why?

96
00:06:24,767 --> 00:06:28,300
I don't know. Maybe because
her family's not well-off.

97
00:06:28,367 --> 00:06:29,567
She's probably intimidated.

98
00:06:29,633 --> 00:06:30,567
I don't know.

99
00:06:32,267 --> 00:06:33,967
Why?

100
00:06:34,033 --> 00:06:35,700
Have you met her mom?

101
00:06:37,100 --> 00:06:38,267
Who is her mom?

102
00:06:41,067 --> 00:06:43,300
No, Mom. I haven't met
her family yet.

103
00:06:49,467 --> 00:06:51,200
We've been separated.

104
00:06:53,400 --> 00:06:55,100
She went to jail.

105
00:06:55,167 --> 00:06:56,133
What?

106
00:06:57,667 --> 00:06:59,767
A horrible person
put her in jail.

107
00:07:06,033 --> 00:07:07,967
- Red's mom...
- His mom?

108
00:07:08,033 --> 00:07:09,400
What happened to Red's mom?

109
00:07:11,400 --> 00:07:14,167
Red's mom is the woman
who put my mom in jail.

110
00:07:15,733 --> 00:07:17,633
Rina is his mom.

111
00:07:21,067 --> 00:07:23,400
She's the person who ruined
our lives.

112
00:07:25,267 --> 00:07:29,867
His family is the reason
why my mom went to jail.

113
00:07:31,933 --> 00:07:34,533
Rina is evil, Raichu.

114
00:07:42,167 --> 00:07:43,333
Red's mom?

115
00:08:02,967 --> 00:08:06,367
Don't worry about what
happened earlier, okay?

116
00:08:07,333 --> 00:08:09,200
I'm sure I will meet
Yenyen soon.

117
00:08:10,567 --> 00:08:12,100
No, Mom.

118
00:08:12,167 --> 00:08:13,733
I'm wondering about
a lot of things.

119
00:08:15,967 --> 00:08:17,933
Don't stress about it.

120
00:08:18,000 --> 00:08:19,633
It won't do you any good.

121
00:08:21,733 --> 00:08:23,133
Don't worry, Mom.

122
00:08:23,200 --> 00:08:26,133
I'm just embarrassed.

123
00:08:26,200 --> 00:08:27,533
I'm sorry.

124
00:08:27,600 --> 00:08:29,033
I'm fine.

125
00:08:29,100 --> 00:08:31,133
As long as you're fine.

126
00:08:31,200 --> 00:08:32,200
Okay?

127
00:08:32,267 --> 00:08:34,667
Why don't you go inside?
Get some rest.

128
00:08:34,733 --> 00:08:35,533
- I'll see you later.
- See you later, Mom.
Okay.

129
00:08:41,233 --> 00:08:42,167
Sabina?
Hello, Auntie!

130
00:08:43,200 --> 00:08:44,567
How's Red?

131
00:08:44,633 --> 00:08:45,700
Oh, dear.

132
00:08:45,767 --> 00:08:47,233
You won't believe what happened.

133
00:08:47,300 --> 00:08:51,033
Yenyen and Red
met at the campus.

134
00:08:51,100 --> 00:08:54,433
I went there to meet her.

135
00:08:54,500 --> 00:08:56,600
And then she disappeared.

136
00:08:56,700 --> 00:08:59,900
She just left without a word.

137
00:08:59,967 --> 00:09:01,767
Unbelievable.

138
00:09:01,833 --> 00:09:03,833
Oh my God. That girl!

139
00:09:03,900 --> 00:09:05,800
She really has no manners!

140
00:09:05,867 --> 00:09:08,633
Look, maybe she had an
emergency or something.

141
00:09:08,700 --> 00:09:11,100
I don't know. I don't want
to think badly of her

142
00:09:11,167 --> 00:09:14,800
since she is important to Red.

143
00:09:14,867 --> 00:09:15,800
I don't know, Auntie.

144
00:09:15,867 --> 00:09:19,867
But I've been on the island
with Yenyen.

145
00:09:19,933 --> 00:09:23,367
Her character is a little shady.

146
00:09:23,433 --> 00:09:25,233
I don't really trust her.

147
00:09:25,300 --> 00:09:26,733
Really?

148
00:09:26,800 --> 00:09:28,467
Yes, Auntie.

149
00:09:28,567 --> 00:09:32,433
I don't want you to hear it
from me

150
00:09:32,500 --> 00:09:36,400
because I don't want you
to think I'm badmouthing her.

151
00:09:36,467 --> 00:09:40,300
Considering that I'm
Red's ex-girlfriend.

152
00:09:40,367 --> 00:09:42,533
Look, what are you
doing tonight?

153
00:09:42,600 --> 00:09:44,700
Why don't you come by the house?

154
00:09:44,767 --> 00:09:46,367
Have dinner with us.

155
00:09:46,433 --> 00:09:50,733
To get Yenyen out of Red's head.

156
00:09:50,800 --> 00:09:51,733
You never know.

157
00:09:51,800 --> 00:09:53,833
You might be the solution
to our problem.

158
00:09:53,900 --> 00:09:55,467
Oh my God, Auntie. Really?

159
00:09:55,533 --> 00:09:56,867
I would love that!

160
00:09:56,933 --> 00:09:57,667
Okay.

161
00:09:57,733 --> 00:09:58,833
All right, see you.

162
00:10:07,867 --> 00:10:09,833
Don't be sad.

163
00:10:09,900 --> 00:10:10,833
We're almost at your house.

164
00:10:10,900 --> 00:10:12,967
Your mom will see you like that.

165
00:10:13,033 --> 00:10:16,033
Don't tell my mom what we
found out about Red, okay?

166
00:10:17,633 --> 00:10:20,533
She still doesn't know
about you and Red?

167
00:10:20,600 --> 00:10:22,367
Haven't you told her yet?

168
00:10:22,433 --> 00:10:24,500
My mom knows about that.

169
00:10:24,567 --> 00:10:26,633
She knows that I've been
on the island with Red.

170
00:10:28,500 --> 00:10:31,100
That I owe my life to him...

171
00:10:31,167 --> 00:10:32,367
that he helped me out a lot.

172
00:10:32,433 --> 00:10:36,133
That's why I made it out alive.

173
00:10:36,233 --> 00:10:39,167
Did she also know about
your relationship?

174
00:10:39,233 --> 00:10:40,867
Of course not!

175
00:10:40,933 --> 00:10:42,633
My mom can't find out...

176
00:10:44,000 --> 00:10:46,567
especially about Red's family.

177
00:10:49,233 --> 00:10:51,400
I don't want her to get hurt.

178
00:10:52,500 --> 00:10:54,600
What will happen to you and Red?

179
00:10:55,867 --> 00:10:57,167
I don't know.

180
00:10:58,167 --> 00:10:59,767
I'm so confused.

181
00:11:02,833 --> 00:11:07,033
How can I love his family
who hurt my mom?

182
00:11:10,100 --> 00:11:13,067
They are the reason why
my mom and I got separated.

183
00:11:15,000 --> 00:11:16,667
What should I do?

184
00:11:18,333 --> 00:11:20,367
I don't know what to do anymore.

185
00:11:29,000 --> 00:11:30,600
Come on.

186
00:11:30,667 --> 00:11:31,600
Let's go.

187
00:11:31,667 --> 00:11:33,700
Let's go inside.
Your mom might see you.

188
00:11:37,233 --> 00:11:40,167
Amanda, let's wait
for this bank to open.

189
00:11:40,233 --> 00:11:42,800
So we don't have to wait
in a long line.

190
00:11:42,900 --> 00:11:47,067
Are you sure this bank
will lend us money?

191
00:11:47,133 --> 00:11:48,733
Why wouldn't they?

192
00:11:48,800 --> 00:11:50,933
We'll use it for
our business anyway.

193
00:11:51,000 --> 00:11:52,067
I know they have a promo going

194
00:11:52,133 --> 00:11:54,700
for small business owners
like us.

195
00:11:54,767 --> 00:11:55,700
Let's give it a try.

196
00:11:56,867 --> 00:11:57,867
Amanda.

197
00:11:59,667 --> 00:12:00,733
Rina's not here.

198
00:12:00,800 --> 00:12:02,733
So you have no one
to pick a fight with.

199
00:12:02,800 --> 00:12:05,167
And please,
don't make a scene here.

200
00:12:05,233 --> 00:12:06,567
I'm respected in this place.

201
00:12:07,733 --> 00:12:09,100
I'm not here to make trouble.

202
00:12:10,133 --> 00:12:12,833
We came here to ask
about a bank loan.

203
00:12:12,900 --> 00:12:14,567
But I don't think
we'll get approved

204
00:12:14,667 --> 00:12:17,233
because it turns out you're
the owner of this bank.

205
00:12:19,000 --> 00:12:20,767
Amanda, we're not bad people.

206
00:12:21,967 --> 00:12:26,033
If we are, then we could have
gotten bad karma for it.

207
00:12:26,100 --> 00:12:27,333
And yet,

208
00:12:27,400 --> 00:12:31,300
our son made it home alive and
safe from that plane crash.

209
00:12:31,367 --> 00:12:33,267
I'm also not a bad person.

210
00:12:33,333 --> 00:12:36,233
Just like you, my daughter
made it back safe and sound.

211
00:12:37,467 --> 00:12:39,400
Come on, Dindi.

212
00:12:39,467 --> 00:12:41,700
We went to the wrong bank.

213
00:12:41,767 --> 00:12:43,967
I'll just borrow money
from other lending companies.

214
00:12:44,033 --> 00:12:45,033
I'm sorry, Amanda.

215
00:12:54,567 --> 00:12:55,500
How are you feeling?

216
00:12:56,700 --> 00:12:57,667
Are you okay now?

217
00:12:58,700 --> 00:13:00,000
No, I'm not.

218
00:13:01,200 --> 00:13:03,600
I still can't accept
what I learned about Red.

219
00:13:05,900 --> 00:13:07,767
I wouldn't also be able
to accept the truth

220
00:13:07,833 --> 00:13:10,067
if I were in your shoes.

221
00:13:10,133 --> 00:13:15,400
If acceptance is that easy,
everyone has already moved on.

222
00:13:17,133 --> 00:13:20,433
Why is the world so small?

223
00:13:20,500 --> 00:13:25,267
Of all the people out there,
why did his mom have to be Rina?

224
00:13:25,367 --> 00:13:28,167
Do you think your mom
won't understand

225
00:13:28,233 --> 00:13:30,467
if you tell her the truth?

226
00:13:30,533 --> 00:13:32,133
Why don't you tell her
the truth?

227
00:13:32,200 --> 00:13:34,667
What do you need to tell me?

228
00:13:44,133 --> 00:13:47,500
What do I need to know?

229
00:13:58,333 --> 00:14:00,033
Yenyen...

230
00:14:00,100 --> 00:14:01,100
what is it?

231
00:14:08,533 --> 00:14:10,000
I'm just messing with you.

232
00:14:10,067 --> 00:14:11,733
What do I need to know?

233
00:14:11,800 --> 00:14:15,467
What are you two talking about?

234
00:14:15,533 --> 00:14:17,567
-It's about...
-Yen, what is it?

235
00:14:17,633 --> 00:14:20,300
It's about the next school year.

236
00:14:21,333 --> 00:14:23,400
Someone offered me
a scholarship.

237
00:14:23,467 --> 00:14:25,467
I don't know if I should
transfer to another school.

238
00:14:25,533 --> 00:14:27,900
That's good news!

239
00:14:28,000 --> 00:14:30,767
At least you have a choice,
right?

240
00:14:30,833 --> 00:14:33,833
Think about it.
You're graduating soon, anyway.

241
00:14:33,900 --> 00:14:36,400
Yes! She can't open up
to you about that.

242
00:14:36,467 --> 00:14:38,033
It's hard, right, Eden?

243
00:14:40,433 --> 00:14:42,100
I'll let you do
what you want to do.

244
00:14:42,167 --> 00:14:45,067
I have no reason to stop you.

245
00:14:45,133 --> 00:14:48,300
As long as you're happy,
I'm all for it.

246
00:14:51,733 --> 00:14:53,300
You two look funny.

247
00:14:53,367 --> 00:14:54,967
I'm going to start cooking.

248
00:15:04,267 --> 00:15:06,167
Eden, I'll finish that.

249
00:15:06,233 --> 00:15:08,133
Go on, get some rest.

250
00:15:08,200 --> 00:15:09,567
I got this, Mom.

251
00:15:09,633 --> 00:15:11,533
You just got back from work,
right?

252
00:15:11,600 --> 00:15:13,467
I can't let you do this too.

253
00:15:15,933 --> 00:15:18,033
I'm not a princess.

254
00:15:18,100 --> 00:15:19,900
I'm used to doing house chores.

255
00:15:19,967 --> 00:15:21,200
I know.

256
00:15:21,267 --> 00:15:24,200
But I'm happy when
I'm taking care of you.

257
00:15:24,267 --> 00:15:27,467
I want to do what
I couldn't do for you before.

258
00:15:27,533 --> 00:15:33,067
Mom, if anyone deserves a VIP
treatment around here, it's you.

259
00:15:33,133 --> 00:15:34,800
- Come here.
- Why?

260
00:15:34,900 --> 00:15:35,767
Come here and sit.

261
00:15:35,833 --> 00:15:37,500
Why?

262
00:15:37,567 --> 00:15:39,333
Sit down.

263
00:15:39,400 --> 00:15:41,233
There you go.

264
00:15:41,300 --> 00:15:44,100
Looks like I'm getting
spoiled here.

265
00:15:46,167 --> 00:15:47,400
Oh, dear.

266
00:15:47,467 --> 00:15:48,733
You know what, Mom?

267
00:15:48,800 --> 00:15:52,533
Once I get a job,
I'll treat you to a spa.

268
00:15:52,600 --> 00:15:53,700
Really?

269
00:15:53,767 --> 00:15:54,933
Yes.

270
00:15:55,000 --> 00:15:58,933
Wow, that's why I'm so grateful
to the guy who saved you.

271
00:15:59,000 --> 00:16:00,400
If it wasn't for him,

272
00:16:00,467 --> 00:16:02,967
I wouldn't be getting
a massage right now.

273
00:16:04,733 --> 00:16:06,533
So, how is he?

274
00:16:06,600 --> 00:16:08,233
When are you going
to introduce him to me?

275
00:16:10,833 --> 00:16:12,767
Hey! Why aren't you
answering me?

276
00:16:13,867 --> 00:16:15,733
Did you see him at school yet?

277
00:16:15,800 --> 00:16:17,133
I haven't seen him yet.

278
00:16:17,200 --> 00:16:20,433
I might see him another day.

279
00:16:20,500 --> 00:16:22,333
But you're going to introduce
him to me, right?

280
00:16:22,400 --> 00:16:23,400
I will.

281
00:16:25,033 --> 00:16:26,300
Just relax, Mom.

282
00:16:27,633 --> 00:16:28,933
Thank you, Eden.

283
00:16:36,500 --> 00:16:39,033
So, how do you like
my orange chicken?

284
00:16:39,100 --> 00:16:40,867
Oh my God, Auntie. I love it!

285
00:16:40,933 --> 00:16:44,033
Actually, it's my first
to try your specialty.

286
00:16:44,133 --> 00:16:45,467
I just love it.

287
00:16:45,533 --> 00:16:48,633
Next time I'm going to make you
try my Paella Negra.

288
00:16:48,700 --> 00:16:50,633
Oh my God! I love that!

289
00:16:50,700 --> 00:16:51,867
I'll look forward to it!

290
00:16:51,933 --> 00:16:52,900
All right.

291
00:16:54,000 --> 00:16:55,767
I'm sorry, I'm not feeling well.

292
00:16:56,767 --> 00:16:58,300
Excuse me.

293
00:16:58,367 --> 00:16:59,300
What's the matter?

294
00:16:59,367 --> 00:17:00,333
Red.

295
00:17:00,400 --> 00:17:02,267
It's okay. I'll take care
of him.

296
00:17:02,333 --> 00:17:03,633
Continue your chitchat.

297
00:17:05,700 --> 00:17:07,667
Well, obviously,

298
00:17:07,733 --> 00:17:10,167
he's still affected by
what happened earlier.

299
00:17:11,433 --> 00:17:12,633
Tell me, Sabina.

300
00:17:13,900 --> 00:17:16,733
What did he like
about that Yenyen?

301
00:17:16,833 --> 00:17:19,867
He's been stranded with Yenyen
on the island for a long time.

302
00:17:21,300 --> 00:17:25,433
I have a feeling that
Yenyen targeted him.

303
00:17:25,500 --> 00:17:27,833
Because she knows that
you guys are rich.

304
00:17:27,900 --> 00:17:31,833
So she's a gold digger?

305
00:17:31,900 --> 00:17:33,800
Well, Auntie,
it's hard to say that,

306
00:17:33,867 --> 00:17:36,433
especially coming from me,
but...

307
00:17:36,500 --> 00:17:40,867
I think it's better
if you meet her.

308
00:17:40,933 --> 00:17:43,867
And see for yourself.

309
00:17:52,000 --> 00:17:54,233
Stop feeling guilty.

310
00:17:54,300 --> 00:17:57,967
You just did what's
best for everyone.

311
00:17:58,033 --> 00:18:00,400
I'm just not used to lying.

312
00:18:00,467 --> 00:18:02,067
I don't like doing it...

313
00:18:02,133 --> 00:18:03,433
especially to my mom.

314
00:18:03,500 --> 00:18:06,867
I want to tell her everything.

315
00:18:06,933 --> 00:18:08,833
But I can't tell her about this

316
00:18:08,900 --> 00:18:10,667
because I don't want her
to get hurt.

317
00:18:14,100 --> 00:18:17,333
Eden, that's what you call
white lies.

318
00:18:17,400 --> 00:18:21,933
And I think she'll understand
if she finds out about Red.

319
00:18:22,033 --> 00:18:23,300
No.

320
00:18:23,367 --> 00:18:26,733
From now on, I will learn
to forget about him.

321
00:18:26,800 --> 00:18:28,067
I'll stay away from him.

322
00:18:29,133 --> 00:18:33,233
I still hate his mom.

323
00:18:33,300 --> 00:18:36,133
I will never forget how
she treated my mom.

324
00:18:37,267 --> 00:18:40,633
It's better if we just break up.

325
00:18:40,700 --> 00:18:43,733
It's hard, but I have to do it.

326
00:18:44,767 --> 00:18:45,700
Eden...

327
00:18:46,967 --> 00:18:49,367
are you not going
to tell him the truth?

328
00:18:49,433 --> 00:18:52,800
You're just going to disappear
from his life?

329
00:18:52,867 --> 00:18:54,900
That's ghosting!
Are you a ghost?

330
00:18:55,000 --> 00:18:57,133
How am I going to tell him?

331
00:18:57,200 --> 00:19:00,000
Should I tell him that
I hate his parents?

332
00:19:00,067 --> 00:19:06,633
Eden, children should not suffer
for what their parents do.

333
00:19:06,700 --> 00:19:09,633
So what does Red has to do
with what his parents did?

334
00:19:09,700 --> 00:19:11,067
Why do you have
to suffer for it?

335
00:19:11,133 --> 00:19:13,100
What do you guys have to do

336
00:19:13,167 --> 00:19:16,167
with your parents' decisions
back then?

337
00:19:16,233 --> 00:19:17,633
You have nothing to do with it!

338
00:19:17,700 --> 00:19:22,500
Red loves his parents so much.

339
00:19:22,567 --> 00:19:25,200
Especially his deceased brother.

340
00:19:25,267 --> 00:19:28,667
What will he think about me
if I tell him the truth?

341
00:19:31,100 --> 00:19:34,233
And how can I love him?

342
00:19:35,500 --> 00:19:37,333
If I'm going to love him,

343
00:19:37,400 --> 00:19:39,933
I have to love his
whole family, too.

344
00:19:41,433 --> 00:19:43,200
But I can't do that.

345
00:19:44,367 --> 00:19:47,733
So it's better if
I stay away from him.

346
00:19:56,700 --> 00:20:01,500
Mr. Akashi, thank you so much!

347
00:20:01,600 --> 00:20:02,500
Thank you very much.

348
00:20:02,567 --> 00:20:04,467
Yes, I got your gift already.

349
00:20:04,533 --> 00:20:06,233
It's sitting on my manto.

350
00:20:06,300 --> 00:20:07,833
Thank you very much.

351
00:20:07,900 --> 00:20:12,367
And I'm very happy that you
are happy with our business.

352
00:20:12,433 --> 00:20:16,233
So many casino addicts
out there.

353
00:20:16,300 --> 00:20:18,900
Yes, I will increase
our collections.

354
00:20:18,967 --> 00:20:20,833
I promise you.

355
00:20:20,900 --> 00:20:22,300
All right.

356
00:20:22,367 --> 00:20:23,700
Thank you, thank you.

357
00:20:23,767 --> 00:20:25,033
I'll see you soon.

358
00:20:25,100 --> 00:20:26,467
Bye, bye.

359
00:20:29,967 --> 00:20:32,467
Rina, why did you call me?

360
00:20:32,533 --> 00:20:33,967
Do you need anything?

361
00:20:34,033 --> 00:20:36,067
I collected everyone's debts.

362
00:20:38,267 --> 00:20:39,833
I can't have peace of mind,
Zandro.

363
00:20:41,900 --> 00:20:43,467
Now that Red is back...

364
00:20:44,533 --> 00:20:46,233
I'm ready to deal with Amanda.

365
00:20:48,100 --> 00:20:51,067
Her daughter should have died
in that plane crash.

366
00:20:52,000 --> 00:20:55,233
That could have been my revenge.

367
00:20:55,300 --> 00:20:57,867
So what do you want me to do?

368
00:20:57,933 --> 00:20:59,033
Do you want me to kill her?

369
00:21:00,033 --> 00:21:00,967
No.

370
00:21:02,267 --> 00:21:04,933
I want to torture Amanda.

371
00:21:06,733 --> 00:21:11,567
We have to get even,
whatever it takes.

372
00:21:22,367 --> 00:21:25,067
Raichu, have you seen Yenyen?

373
00:21:25,133 --> 00:21:27,033
I'm texting someone.

374
00:21:27,100 --> 00:21:28,133
Raichu, if you've seen her,

375
00:21:28,200 --> 00:21:29,733
can you please tell me
where she is?

376
00:21:31,600 --> 00:21:32,733
I don't know where she is.

377
00:21:36,567 --> 00:21:38,267
I don't believe you.

378
00:21:40,533 --> 00:21:42,933
Wow! Judgmental!

379
00:21:43,033 --> 00:21:45,333
Why would I lie to you?

380
00:21:48,033 --> 00:21:50,067
Just tell me where she lives.

381
00:21:51,600 --> 00:21:55,833
I won't tell you even if
I know where she lives.

382
00:21:55,900 --> 00:21:58,567
And they moved yesterday.

383
00:22:05,100 --> 00:22:06,433
Raichu, please.

384
00:22:07,700 --> 00:22:09,133
I couldn't get a hold of her.

385
00:22:09,200 --> 00:22:10,867
I was going to introduce her
to my mom.

386
00:22:10,933 --> 00:22:13,900
But she disappeared.

387
00:22:13,967 --> 00:22:16,600
I don't know where to find her.
I don't know where to go.

388
00:22:18,433 --> 00:22:21,167
Raichu, please, if you see her,

389
00:22:21,233 --> 00:22:24,267
can you tell her that
I'm looking for her?

390
00:22:26,400 --> 00:22:29,967
I've been losing sleep
thinking about her.

391
00:22:34,200 --> 00:22:38,633
Tell her that I'll look for her
wherever she goes.

392
00:22:40,900 --> 00:22:43,700
And please remind her of
our promise to each other.

393
00:22:45,933 --> 00:22:49,367
We promised that
we would never part.

394
00:22:52,400 --> 00:22:53,533
Raichu, I've been...

395
00:22:56,067 --> 00:22:58,167
I've been good to her.

396
00:23:02,767 --> 00:23:03,633
I hope...

397
00:23:03,700 --> 00:23:05,100
I hope she won't abandon me.

398
00:23:09,200 --> 00:23:16,133
I hope she'll have the courage
to tell me how she feels.

399
00:23:38,667 --> 00:23:39,967
I did what you asked me to do.

400
00:23:40,033 --> 00:23:41,633
I robbed the woman.

401
00:23:41,700 --> 00:23:43,333
Consider your debt paid off.

402
00:23:43,400 --> 00:23:45,333
It was you! You bastard!

403
00:23:46,433 --> 00:23:48,800
He's Rina's brother.

404
00:23:48,867 --> 00:23:51,400
Rina had you robbed
to get revenge on you.

405
00:23:51,467 --> 00:23:53,067
I can't let this slide!

406
00:23:53,133 --> 00:23:55,367
What if they try to hurt Yenyen?

407
00:23:55,467 --> 00:23:58,967
I will let Rina know that
I'm not afraid of her!

408
00:23:59,033 --> 00:24:03,167
Why does our family has to
cross paths with Rina's family?

409
00:24:03,233 --> 00:24:05,533
I even cross paths with her son.

410
00:24:05,600 --> 00:24:06,700
What do you mean by that?

411
00:24:06,767 --> 00:24:09,567
The guy who got stranded
with me on the island...

412
00:24:09,633 --> 00:24:11,467
Red is Rina's son.

413
00:24:11,533 --> 00:24:12,733
OMG!

414
00:24:12,800 --> 00:24:14,367
- What do you want?
- I'm here to collect your debt.

415
00:24:14,433 --> 00:24:15,800
We don't owe you anything!

416
00:24:15,867 --> 00:24:17,767
Yes, you do! You owe me a lot!

417
00:24:17,833 --> 00:24:21,567
And I know you're using
your brother

418
00:24:21,633 --> 00:24:22,933
to make my life miserable!

419
00:24:23,000 --> 00:24:24,000
Tell your brother
to come out here!

420
00:24:24,067 --> 00:24:26,467
- Zandro won't be facing you.
- Oh, really?

421
00:24:28,300 --> 00:24:29,967
Mom, no!

422
00:24:30,033 --> 00:24:31,967
Now, tell me.

423
00:24:32,033 --> 00:24:34,467
Where do you want
your head to drop?

424
00:24:34,533 --> 00:24:37,067
On your right or your left?
